    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4338624">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4338624">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4338624)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4338624">
																		Maybe I&#039;m just confused
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aceofmoxes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2943332); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2943332&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204186" alt="Aceofmoxes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2943332)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aceofmoxes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2943332); return false;" >Aceofmoxes</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566590950 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Aug 2019 20:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4338624">
									

<p>There's a lot of this article that doesn't make sense to me.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the Altruist-9 was constructed with a faster-than-light (FTL) drive and high efficiency solar sails.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Why bother with solar sails if you also have FTL? Solar sails have a top speed that's under .1% of lightspeed. Most FLT systems aren't additive with non-FTL tech, either. Is it supposed to 'jump' through to the target, then float around the star system? It sounds like it crashes and was always meant to crash.</p>
<p>Who is in the cryo camber? Who contacted the foundation through the wormhole? Was O<sub>2</sub>-less Earth home to a foundation that studied anomalies in the wild, without containment? But they didn't let the man who hated anomalies out.</p>

							</div>

								
					
						<div class="options">
				
													<strong><a href="javascript:;" onclick="postReply(event,4338624)" class="btn btn-primary btn-small btn-sm">Reply</a></strong> 
																	<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostOptions(event,4338624)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Options</a>
							</div>
									
			<div id="post-options-4338624" class="options" style="display: none">
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="short">
							<a class="options btn btn-default btn-mini btn-xs" href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4338624)" c>Unfold</a>
						<a class="title" href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4338624)">Maybe I&#039;m just confused</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aceofmoxes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2943332); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2943332&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204186" alt="Aceofmoxes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2943332)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aceofmoxes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2943332); return false;" >Aceofmoxes</a></span>, <span class="odate time_1566590950 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Aug 2019 20:09</span>
		</div>
	</div>
 
                
        
                      
    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4338665">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4338665">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4338665)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4338665">
																		Re: Maybe I&#039;m just confused
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/billith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3042342); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3042342&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204186" alt="Billith" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3042342)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/billith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3042342); return false;" >Billith</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566593016 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Aug 2019 20:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4338665">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">confused&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;way&nbsp;to&nbsp;be</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>FTL travel has its fair share of issues. The exotic matter emits a quantized field and FTL travel doesn't change that, it's the other way around. The solar sails provide means of charging and for local travel that doesn't need the unnecessary power</li>
<li>what do you mean by &quot;aren't additive&quot;? FTL drives don't really exist afaik, and in the realm of fantasy, having additional means to control the ship more accurately is not unheard of</li>
<li>It was meant to crash only if the wormhole reappears</li>
<li>The cryo-chamber contains who the New Earth Foundation considers The Founder, but not really the true Founder as they are off-world. They also have different views on anomalies</li>
<li>The notes at the end indicate everything was orchestrated by the Foundation, but this Foundation has transcended.</li>
<li>The O2 thing relates to the great oxygenation event of our planet which happened 2ish billion years ago.</li>
<li>The Foundation studied and used anomalies instead of fearing them and containing them from the world. There is no masquerade on Earth Prime. This is explained in more detail in <a href="/richard-larenz-personal-log">Richard Larenz Personal Log</a> and <a href="/a-place-to-call-your-home">A Place to Call Your Home</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Any other questions?</p>
</div>
</div>
