			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4339633">
									

<p>I hate to sound like I'm beating a dead horse since I've posted largely the same thing on other postings of this article, but since you asked: I think the article takes too long to get off the ground, the extremely truncated transcripts are kind of tiresome to deal with, and the ultimate conclusion of the article doesn't hit me emotionally or otherwise. It feels like too much extraneous setup, which I imagine relates to your broader planned cannon, but is not an enjoyable reading experience.</p>
<p>There's not much you can do about my personal preferences obviously, but I would still strongly recommend reconsidering the volume of garbled logs at the start if nothing else.</p>

							</div>

								
