			<div class="content" id="post-content-4339654">
									

<p>If you’re attached to the text formatting, there could also be less text in that section overall. Making my way through it just felt like I was being forced to endure something unpleasant to get to the rest of the story. People who enjoy deciphering things more may feel differently.</p>
<p>Also, I don’t entirely remember the last version’s structure, and this does stand on its own as a piece, but it still gave me the impression that there was supposed to be much more to come on top of it later. That may be a reflection of the fact that I know you planned addition content in this setting. Either way, something can still stand on its own while introducing so many new things to be explore that it feels more introductory than anything else, and I think this falls into that category.</p>

							</div>

								
